{"id":"287732329_Recommendations_about_nomenclature_for_papers_submitted_to_Zootaxa","abstract":"The rapid success of Zootaxa has been due in part to the decentralization of its editorial process and to the taxonomic specialization of members of the editorial board (Zhang 2010). Both these factors allowed a quicker publication of papers than in many other journals, after an appropriate review by editors well acquainted with the taxa covered and the relevant literature.","authors":["Alain Dubois","Alessandro Minelli","ZHI-QIANG ZHANG"],"meta":["July 2011Zootaxa 2943(2943):58-62","DOI:10.11646/zootaxa.2943.1.3"],"references":["334025036_Updating_the_Linnaean_Heritage_Names_as_Tools_for_Thinking_about_Animals_and_Plants_cover","281131228_Genitives_of_species_and_subspecies_nomina_derived_from_personal_names_should_not_be_emended","268076883_Contributions_to_a_List_of_First_Reviser_actions_Ornithology","254714261_Does_nomenclatural_availability_of_nomina_of_new_species_or_subspecies_require_the_deposition_of_vouchers_in_collections","292016640_Types_in_modern_taxonomy","289966077_Page_priority_does_not_exist_in_the_Code_Neomegalotomus_parvus_Westwood_1842_has_precedence_over_Neomegalotomus_simplex_Westwood_1842_Hemiptera_Heteroptera_Alydidae","287612695_Retroactive_changes_should_be_introduced_in_the_Code_only_with_great_care_problems_related_to_the_spellings_of_nomina","285486208_Reviving_Descriptive_Taxonomy_after_250_Years_Promising_Signs_from_a_Mega-Journal_in_Taxonomy","274219971_The_International_Code_of_Zoological_Nomenclature_as_a_Guide_to_the_Pronunciation_of_Zoological_Latin","250067396_International_Code_of_Zoological_Nomenclature_Fourth_Edition"]}